tComponentid.name: tComponentid
tComponentid.description: This group defines the attributes common to all components. This group is required.

a1Installation.name: a1Installation
a1Installation.description: The time and date when this component was installed.

a1Verify.name: a1Verify
a1Verify.description: A code that provides a level of verification that the component is still installed and working.

tIcmbState.name: tIcmbState
tIcmbState.description: Access to information on basic chassis features.

a12ChassisAvailable.name: a12ChassisAvailable
a12ChassisAvailable.description: This attribute indicates whether the chassis is currently visible on the ICMB.

a12IcmbId.name: a12IcmbId
a12IcmbId.description: This is the bus ID of the chassis' ICMB bridge.

a12SdrDeviceId.name: a12SdrDeviceId
a12SdrDeviceId.description: This is the IMB address of the device providing access to the chassis Sensor Data Repository. A value of 0xff indicates there is no such device known.

a12SelDeviceId.name: a12SelDeviceId
a12SelDeviceId.description: This is the IMB address of the device providing access to thechassis System Event Log.A value of 0xff indicates there is no such device known.

a12SmDeviceId.name: a12SmDeviceId
a12SmDeviceId.description: This is the IMB address of the device providing access to thechassis System Management software.A value of 0xff indicates there is no such device known.

a12SdrReadState.name: a12SdrReadState
a12SdrReadState.description: This attribute indicates whether the chassis SDR is used topopulate the sensor tables

a12EventPollingPeriod.name: a12EventPollingPeriod
a12EventPollingPeriod.description: This is the period in seconds between polls for new chassisevent . A value of 0 disables polling.

a12EventCount.name: a12EventCount
a12EventCount.description: This is the number of chassis events generated.

a12ManageChassis.name: a12ManageChassis
a12ManageChassis.description: This indicates whether events should be generated for this chassis

a12SetAvailablityState.name: a12SetAvailablityState
a12SetAvailablityState.description: Sets chassis availability state. Writing zero to this attribute instructs the chassis to become unavailable. Writing non-zero instructs the chassis to become available.

tOperationalState.name: tOperationalState
tOperationalState.description: This group provides the operational state, usage, and availabili y status, and administrative state indicators for specific Device Group instance .

a31OperationalStateInstanceIndex.name: a31OperationalStateInstanceIndex
a31OperationalStateInstanceIndex.description: The Index into the Operational State table.

a31DeviceGroupIndex.name: a31DeviceGroupIndex
a31DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this instance.

a31OperationalStatus.name: a31OperationalStatus
a31OperationalStatus.description: The operational status of the Device Group instance.

a31UsageState.name: a31UsageState
a31UsageState.description: The usage state of the Device Group instance.

a31AvailabilityStatus.name: a31AvailabilityStatus
a31AvailabilityStatus.description: The availability status of the Device Group instance.

a31AdministrativeState.name: a31AdministrativeState
a31AdministrativeState.description: The administrative state of the Device Group instance.

a31FatalErrorCount.name: a31FatalErrorCount
a31FatalErrorCount.description: The accumulated Fatal or Non-recoverable error count for this Device Group instance.

a31MajorErrorCount.name: a31MajorErrorCount
a31MajorErrorCount.description: The accumulated Major or Critical error count for this Device Group instance.

a31WarningErrorCount.name: a31WarningErrorCount
a31WarningErrorCount.description: The accumulated Warning or Non-Critical error count for this Device Group instance.

a31CurrentErrorStatus.name: a31CurrentErrorStatus
a31CurrentErrorStatus.description: This attribute presents the current error status for this Device Group instance. The most critical error status in effect should be presented. I.e. if a part of the Device Group instance is 'Critical', while other status is 'Non-critical' then the status'Critical' should be reported.

tFieldReplaceableUnit.name: tFieldReplaceableUnit
tFieldReplaceableUnit.description: A Field Replaceable Unit (FRU), is defined as a hardware component which is designed to be separately removable for replacement or repair. For the purposes of this definition, a motherboard and a fixed hard disk are FRUs, whereas a fixed hard disk platter or a chip fixed in place on the motherboard are not FRUs since they are not designed to be separately removable. Each instance within the FRU table should contain the device group and instance data for the associated hardware component.

a93FruIndex.name: a93FruIndex
a93FruIndex.description: The index into the Field Replaceable Unit table.

a93DeviceGroupIndex.name: a93DeviceGroupIndex
a93DeviceGroupIndex.description: The group ID of the group referencing this Field Replaceable Unitinstance.

a93Description.name: a93Description
a93Description.description: A clear description of this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93Manufacturer.name: a93Manufacturer
a93Manufacturer.description: The name of the company manufacturing or providing this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93Model.name: a93Model
a93Model.description: The manufacturer's model number for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93PartNumber.name: a93PartNumber
a93PartNumber.description: A part number by which a replacement part can be ordered for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93FruSerialNumber.name: a93FruSerialNumber
a93FruSerialNumber.description: The manufacturer's serial number for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93RevisionLevel.name: a93RevisionLevel
a93RevisionLevel.description: The revision level of this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93WarrantyStartDate.name: a93WarrantyStartDate
a93WarrantyStartDate.description: The start date of the service warranty for this Field Replaceabl Unit.

a93WarrantyDuration.name: a93WarrantyDuration
a93WarrantyDuration.description: The total duration of this Field Replaceable Unit warranty in months.

a93SupportPhoneNumber.name: a93SupportPhoneNumber
a93SupportPhoneNumber.description: The phone number(s) for support for this Field Replaceable Unit.

a93FruInternetUniformResourceLocator.name: a93FruInternetUniformResourceLocator
a93FruInternetUniformResourceLocator.description: The Internet Uniform Resource Locator string that can be used through a World Wide Web browser to obtain further information about this FRU

a116EventType.name: a116EventType
a116EventType.description: The type of event that has occurred.

a116IsEventState_based.name: a116IsEventState_based
a116IsEventState_based.description: The value of this attribute determines whether the Event being reported is a state-based Event or not. If the value of this attribute is TRUE then the Event is state-based. Otherwise the Event is not state-based.

a116EventStateKey.name: a116EventStateKey
a116EventStateKey.description: A unique, single integer key into the Event State group if this is a state-based Event. If this is not a state-based Event then this attribute's value is not defined.

a116AssociatedGroup.name: a116AssociatedGroup
a116AssociatedGroup.description: The class name of the group that is associated with the events defined in this Event Generation group.

a116EventSystem.name: a116EventSystem
a116EventSystem.description: The major functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

a116EventSubsystem.name: a116EventSubsystem
a116EventSubsystem.description: The minor functional aspect of the product causing the fault.

tPhysicalContainerGlobalTable.name: tPhysicalContainerGlobalTable
tPhysicalContainerGlobalTable.description: This group of attributes describes the fields in a row of the Physical Container Global Table. This table lists all of the containers (e.g. chassis, sub-chassis, etc.) included within the component whose structure is being described.

a127ContainerOrChassisType.name: a127ContainerOrChassisType
a127ContainerOrChassisType.description: The type of container or chassis.

a127AssetTag.name: a127AssetTag
a127AssetTag.description: The Container asset tag string.This asset tag string is writeabl by the system administrator.

a127ChassisLockPresent.name: a127ChassisLockPresent
a127ChassisLockPresent.description: If true, a chassis lock is present on the Container.

a127BootupState.name: a127BootupState
a127BootupState.description: The current state of this system when it booted.

a127PowerState.name: a127PowerState
a127PowerState.description: The current state of the power supply for this system.

a127ThermalState.name: a127ThermalState
a127ThermalState.description: The current thermal state of this Container.

a127FruGroupIndex.name: a127FruGroupIndex
a127FruGroupIndex.description: If this is a Field Replaceable Unit or if it is part of another FRU, this provides an index into the FRU table; 'value = -1' indicates that the group is not a FRU.

a127OperationalGroupIndex.name: a127OperationalGroupIndex
a127OperationalGroupIndex.description: The index into the Operational State table for this device if applicable.

a127ContainerIndex.name: a127ContainerIndex
a127ContainerIndex.description: A unique index for the Physical Container in Physical Container Global Table.

a127ContainerName.name: a127ContainerName
a127ContainerName.description: This is any 64-octet long name that the user or system administr tor wishes to give this specific physical container.

a127ContainerLocation.name: a127ContainerLocation
a127ContainerLocation.description: This attribute is a string name for the location of the containe . This attribute is Read-Write and may be set to any appropriate value by the user. The string may be 128 octets long.

a127ContainerSecurityStatus.name: a127ContainerSecurityStatus
a127ContainerSecurityStatus.description: This attribute describes whether the Container is physically secure or not. This includes the state of the door lock, or the boot devices or the keyboard or mouse.

tMiftomib.name: tMiftomib
tMiftomib.description: This group defines attributes required for DMI to SNMP translati n.

a1001MibName.name: a1001MibName
a1001MibName.description: The MIB name that defines this MIF

a1001MibOid.name: a1001MibOid
a1001MibOid.description: The MIB Object Identifier that corresponds to this MIF

a1001DisableTrap.name: a1001DisableTrap
a1001DisableTrap.description: This attribute can be changed to disable sending oftraps from this component

tSystemControl.name: tSystemControl
tSystemControl.description: Status and control of global system control features.

a1004Selfid.name: a1004Selfid
a1004Selfid.description: A unique number that identifies this row.

a1004ResetSystem.name: a1004ResetSystem
a1004ResetSystem.description: Writing to the attribute initiates an immediate system hard reset. The value for this attribute is either Do Not Reset or Initiate Reset.

a1004TimedResetIncrement.name: a1004TimedResetIncrement
a1004TimedResetIncrement.description: This attribute contains the increments in which a timed reset can be set, in microseconds.

a1004TimedResetResolution.name: a1004TimedResetResolution
a1004TimedResetResolution.description: This attribute contains the resolution to which a Timed Reset can be set, in microseconds. For example, a resolution of 1 second and an increment of 10 seconds would indicate that a 10 second delay interval setting produces a 9 to 10 second delay.

a1004TimeUntilSystemReset.name: a1004TimeUntilSystemReset
a1004TimeUntilSystemReset.description: This attribute contains the interval for timed resets, in units of the Timed Reset Increment attribute. Writing a non-zero value, and setting the Timed Reset Enable on, initiates a timed reset countdown.

a1004SystemPowerCapabilities.name: a1004SystemPowerCapabilities
a1004SystemPowerCapabilities.description: This attribute describes the system power control capabilities. It can have one of the following values: Unknown, On And Off, Off Only, or On Only.

a1004SystemPowerStatus.name: a1004SystemPowerStatus
a1004SystemPowerStatus.description: This attribute provides access to the status and control of system power. Its value is either On or Off.

a1004EventLoggingCapability.name: a1004EventLoggingCapability
a1004EventLoggingCapability.description: This attribute describes the Event Logging Capabilities. The attribute value can be : Unknown, Unsupported, Active, or Inactive. If the Event logging capability is Active, the BIOS logs the system errors to the FLASH. The LSC reads this FLASH log and takes appropriate actions. If this feature is Inactive, the LSC will read the values from the system registers directly. The Event logging capability can be set to Active or Inactive using the System Configuration Utility (SCU).

a1004WatchdogTimerIncrement.name: a1004WatchdogTimerIncrement
a1004WatchdogTimerIncrement.description: This attribute contains the increments in which a watchdog update interval can be set. This value is maintained internally by instrumentati n code in microseconds. In LSC Local Console, this value is shown in Seconds.

a1004WatchdogTimerResolution.name: a1004WatchdogTimerResolution
a1004WatchdogTimerResolution.description: Resolution to which a watchdog update interval can be set. For example, a watchdog timer resolution of R microsecond and an watchdog timer increment of I microseconds would indicate that a watchdog update interva setting of N will produce a (N*I)-R to (N*I) microseconds delay. In LSC Local Console, this value is shown in Seconds.

a1004WatchdogUpdateInterval.name: a1004WatchdogUpdateInterval
a1004WatchdogUpdateInterval.description: This attribute specifies the Interval for watchdog resets, in minutes. If the system software does not update the watchdog timer within this interval, a hard reset will occur. Selecting a non-zero value for this attribute and setting the Use System Watchdog Feature attribute to 'On' starts the watchdog reset timer countdown.

a1004UseSystemWatchdogFeature.name: a1004UseSystemWatchdogFeature
a1004UseSystemWatchdogFeature.description: If this value is On, then the Watchdog feature is enabled and the Watchdog Update Interval value is valid. If enabled this feature automatically resets the server if the LSC software does not reset the watchdog timer within the specified Watchdog Update Interval. NOTE : This is a hard reset that will immediately reset the system without taking NetWare down. This might result in some files being corrupted.

a1004ResetSystemAfterDelay.name: a1004ResetSystemAfterDelay
a1004ResetSystemAfterDelay.description: This attribute controls whether or not the timed reset function is enabled. If the value is On, then the system will reset when the Timed Reset Interval expires.

a1004SavePersistentData.name: a1004SavePersistentData
a1004SavePersistentData.description: When this attribute value is set to ON all the persistent data like thresholds are stored into the persistent data Table.

a1004RestoreFactoryDefaults.name: a1004RestoreFactoryDefaults
a1004RestoreFactoryDefaults.description: When this attribute value is set to ON all the Factory default thresholds are restored.

a1004ShutdownOs.name: a1004ShutdownOs
a1004ShutdownOs.description: Writing to this attribute initiates an immediate OS shutdown. The value of this attribute is either Do Not Shutdown or Shutdown OS.

a1004ShutdownOsAndPowerOff.name: a1004ShutdownOsAndPowerOff
a1004ShutdownOsAndPowerOff.description: Writing to this attribute initiates an immediate OS shutdown and Power Off of the system. The value of this attribute is either Do Not Shutdown and Power Off or Shutdown OS and Power Off.

a1004ShutdownOsAndHardwareReset.name: a1004ShutdownOsAndHardwareReset
a1004ShutdownOsAndHardwareReset.description: Writing to this attribute initiates an immediate OS shutdown. The value of this attribute is either Do Not Shutdown and Hardware Reset or Shutdown OS and Hardware Reset.

a1004IssueAHardwareNmi.name: a1004IssueAHardwareNmi
a1004IssueAHardwareNmi.description: Writing to this attribute causes a hardware NMI (Non Maskabale Interrup). It will have one of the two values. Issue an NMI, or Do Not Issue an NMI

a2000DimContext.name: a2000DimContext
a2000DimContext.description: Opaque data used by DIM objects to obtain their context informat on from some invocating source. It is assumed that the DIMs will be able to usefully parse the information in this attribute, as the 'mainline' DMI code in the CI makes no attempt to understand it.

a2000PersistentDataWriteDelay.name: a2000PersistentDataWriteDelay
a2000PersistentDataWriteDelay.description: Defines the timeout from an attribute set operation until the presistent write operation is invoked. If another set operation takes place during this period, the timeout timer is reset back to this value, so a persistent write operation will only take place after the specified period has elasped with no set operations. Timeout is specified in 1/10 second quantity. If set to zero, no persistent write operation will occur.

a2000EifInterfaceName.name: a2000EifInterfaceName
a2000EifInterfaceName.description: EIF Interface Name used to distinguish the component type this MIF file represents.
